org.jooby.json

Class Jackson

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jooby.json.Jackson
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Jooby.Module

    public class Jackson
extends Object
implements Jooby.Module

    jackson

    JSON support from the excellent Jackson library. This module provides a JSON Parser and Renderer, but also an ObjectMapper.

    usage

     {
   use(new Jackson());

   // sending
   get("/my-api", req  -> new MyObject());

   // receiving a json body
   post("/my-api", req  -> {
     MyObject obj = req.body(MyObject.class);
     return obj;
   });

   // receiving a json param from a multipart or form url encoded
   post("/my-api", req  -> {
     MyObject obj = req.param("my-object").to(MyObject.class);
     return obj;
   });
 }

    views

    Dynamic views are supported via JacksonView:

    
 {
   use(new Jackson());

   get("/public", req -> {
     Item item = ...;
     return new JacksonView<>(Views.Public.class, item);
   });

   get("/public", req -> {
     Item item = ...;
     return new JacksonView<>(Views.Internal.class, item);
   });
 }

    advanced configuration

    If you need a special setting or configuration for your ObjectMapper: 

     {
   use(new Jackson().configure(mapper  -> {
     // setup your custom object mapper
   });
 }
    or provide an ObjectMapper instance: 
     {
   ObjectMapper mapper = ....;
   use(new Jackson(mapper));
 }
    It is possible to wire Jackson modules too: 
     {

   use(new Jackson()
      .module(MyJacksonModuleWiredByGuice.class)
   );
 }
    This is useful when your jackson module require some dependencies.
    Since:
    0.6.0
    Author:
    edgar
